sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Transcriptional Regulator and cioAB expression platform
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the expression platform for our brand new biobricks. We want both the cioAB gene complex to express constitutively so the bacteria, in this case E. coli, can resist to diferent levels of cyanide. We also want the transcriptional regulator to be constitutive because it will interact with the cyanide to further activate activate the inducible promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The transcriptional regulator come from Pseudomonas pseudoalcaligenes, the cioAB gene complex come from Pseudomonas aeruginosa and the other genes are well characterized biobricks from the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We are working very hard with this construct for further characterization.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944011
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CioAB genes code for a cyanide-insensitive terminal oxidase that gives bacteria another pathway for the electrons transport. In this part, it is coupled with a reporter gene (GFP) and a terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This biobrick is product of a ligation from part BBa_K944006 and BBa_K944008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No considerations right now.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: T7 constitutive promoter with RBS, transcriptional regulator from de cyanide inducible promoter and
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This BioBrick is the ligation of the biobrick BBa_K944009 and the biobrick BBa_K944010 which is an intermediate part to form our composite part which aims to express the cioAB cyanide-insensitive terminal oxidase related to the cytochrome bd quinol oxidases.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Most of the parts of this intermediate construct are well characterized biobricks from the registry except for the transcriptional regulator which is a brand new biobrick we add to the registry.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No considerations right now.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
CioAB has an important role in allowing aerobic respiration under cyanogenic growth conditions, because it encodes the subunits of a terminal oxidase homologous to the cytochrome bd quinol oxidases in bacteria. Under low oxygen tensions, these proteins provide an alternative to electrons transport.
We used this part to give resistance to cyanide to our bacteria under low oxygen tension.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This biobrick is product of a ligation from CioA and CioB.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No considerations right now.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Transcriptional Regulator for Cyanide Inducible Promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cynF gene codes for a sigma ?54-dependent transcriptional regulator of 648-amino-acid residues, which belongs to the FIS (factor for inversion stimulation) family of regulatory proteins. P. pseudoalcaligenes CynF shared 59% identity with R. palustris CynF (YP_485671) and 58% identity with Bradyrhizobium japonicum CynF (NP_772375). This Transcriptional regulator works along with the cyanide and cyanide compounds inducible promoter in the natural ocurring cyanase operon from P. pseudoalcaligenes.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part came from the genomic sequence of Pseudomonas pseudoalcaligenes CECT5344 and was synthesized by IDT technologies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part had 3 illegal Pst1 restriction sites.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cioA gene related to cyanide insensitivity
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: cioA encodes a hydrophobic protein of 488 amino acid residues with a predicted molecular mass of 54241 Da.cioA form part of the cioAB operon from Pseudomonas aeruginosa which code for a novel cyanide-insensitive terminal oxidase related to the cytochrome bd quinol oxidases.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This came from the Pseudomonas aeruginosa genomic sequence we searched in genbank and synthesized by IDT Technologies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part has no restriction sites used in the protocol standard 10.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K944004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cioB gene related to cyanide insensitivity
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: cioB encodes a protein, which has the characteristics of a membrane protein, containing 335 amino acids with a predicted molecular mass of 3706 Da. cioB form part of the cioAB operon from Pseudomonas aeruginosa which code for a novel cyanide-insensitive terminal oxidase related to the cytochrome bd quinol oxidases.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Natasha G??mez
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part came from the Pseudomonas aeruginosa genomic sequence and synthesized by IDT Technologies.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The cioB naturaly had a Pst1 restriction site in its sequence so we did a silent mutation for no longer to be this restriction site and proceed with the standard protocol 10.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
